# JSDoc Documentation Rules

All functions must include JSDoc documentation.

JSDoc must describe:

- function purpose
- parameters
- return values
- behavior
- edge cases

---

Example

/\*\*

- Validates login credentials.
-
- @param email user email
- @param password user password
- @returns boolean indicating validation result
-
- This function checks the format of the provided credentials
- before sending the authentication request.
  \*/

Functions without JSDoc are considered incomplete.
